_:N3abb3b4c3d2e4bea86ca8a80197b8e09 <http://schema.org/text> "The internal audit profession involves providing independent assurance and advisory services to organizations, evaluating and improving the effectiveness of governance, risk management, and control processes. " <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/jsonld> .
_:N3abb3b4c3d2e4bea86ca8a80197b8e09 <http://schema.org/articleBody> "<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>The Internal Audit Profession is one of the <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/civil-service/about/recruitment#professions\">Civil Service Professions</a> and focuses on assessing the management of the main risks to effective public service delivery.</p>\n\n<p>The auditors base their assurance on objective assessments of the framework of governance, risk management and control.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"career-opportunities-and-professional-development\">Career opportunities and professional development</h2>\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/civil-service-internal-audit-profession\">Internal Audit Profession website</a> is the place where you can engage with your professional community and find out about the learning, qualifications and opportunities available to help you develop your skills.</p>\n</div>" <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/jsonld> .
